 When the existing leader fails, a new leader for  Consistent Core is elected. Once elected, the new leader starts tracking the leases.
 The new leader refreshes all the leases it knows about. Note that the leases which were about to expire on the old leader get extended by the &#39;time to live&#39; value. This is not a problem, as it gives the chance for the client to reconnect with the new leader and continue the lease.
